 (within 1 year) when you can be released on licence.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/guide-to-probation/ask-to-be-released-again-on-probation","slug":"ask-to-be-released-again-on-probation","order":5,"title":"Ask to be released again on probation","body":"<p>If you have been taken back to prison and you think you should be released from prison on probation again, you can ask the parole board. This is called &lsquo;making representations&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<p>You can speak to the parole board yourself, or ask a family member, friend or legal adviser to do it.</p>\n\n<p>You must do this within 2 weeks of being told why you are being recalled to prison.</p>\n"}]},"tags":[{"title":"Prisons and probation","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice%2Fprisons-probation.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Sentencing, probation and support for families of prisoners","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice%2Fprisons-probation","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice/prisons-probation"},"parent":{"title":"Crime, justice and the law","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/justice.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Legal processes, courts and the police","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=justice","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/justice"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/leaving-prison.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/leaving-prison","title":"Leaving prison","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:17:07+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/community-sentences.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/community-sentences","title":"Community sentences","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-10-25T10:35:11+00:00"}]},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/staying-in-touch-with-someone-in-prison.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/staying-in-touch-with-someone-in-prison","title":"Staying